# This self-contained module pins Bazel 8 (.bazelversion) rather than inheriting
# gale's root 9.1.0. rules_renode (pinned 5fc76ad, == upstream HEAD) is authored
# against Bazel 8: its renode/defs.bzl uses the PyInfo / py_* / sh_* globals and
# the old rules_shell runfiles_impl single-file behavior. Bazel 8 still provides
# these via the default --incompatible_autoload_externally migration set; Bazel 9
# emptied that set (migration window closed), so on 9.1 the module fails to LOAD
# ("PyInfo not defined") and then ANALYZE ("runfiles_impl must produce a single
# file"). Upstream's own CI uses bazelisk-latest with no .bazelversion, i.e.
# Bazel 8 — so 8.x is the known-good configuration. Reported to renode-bazel-rules.

# rules_renode transitively pulls rules_python 1.7.0; the module declares 0.36.0
# as a direct dep. The resolved 1.7.0 is fine — silence the direct-dependency
# version-skew error rather than pin a stale rules_python.
common --check_direct_dependencies=off
